## `pub fn watch(&self, path: &str, recursive: bool) -> Result<Watcher>`
<!-- checksum: rust-fs-2c -->

### Purpose
Subscribe to mutation events on this `Filesystem`. Returns a `Watcher` whose `Drop` unsubscribes.

### Preconditions
- `path` resolves to a directory.
- Caller has `R` on the watched directory.

### Postconditions
- Events emitted by any mutator that match the watcher's scope (see `watch.rs` `path_matches` rules) are queued on the watcher's channel.

### Implementation Notes

```rust
impl Filesystem {
    pub fn watch(&self, path: &str, recursive: bool) -> Result<Watcher> {
        let ino = self.resolve_to_inode(path)?;
        let row = nodes::get(&self.conn, ino)?;
        if row.kind != NodeKind::Dir {
            return Err(Error::NotADirectory(format!("{path:?} is not a directory")));
        }
        crate::perms::require_access(
            row.mode, row.uid, row.gid,
            self.caller_uid, self.caller_gid,
            Access::R,
        )?;
        Ok(WatchRegistry::subscribe(&self.watchers, path.to_string(), recursive))
    }

    fn path_for_inode(&self, inode: u64) -> Option<String> {
        // Reverse-lookup: take any entry pointing at `inode` and reconstruct
        // its path by walking parents up to root via entries.parent_of.
        let mut stmt = self.conn.prepare(
            "SELECT parent, name FROM entries WHERE inode = ?1 LIMIT 1",
        ).ok()?;
        let (mut parent, mut name): (u64, String) = stmt.query_row(
            rusqlite::params![inode as i64],
            |r| Ok((r.get::<_, i64>(0)? as u64, r.get::<_, String>(1)?)),
        ).ok()?;
        let mut parts = vec![name.clone()];
        while parent != ROOT_INODE {
            let (gp, gn): (u64, String) = self.conn.query_row(
                "SELECT parent, name FROM entries WHERE inode = ?1 LIMIT 1",
                rusqlite::params![parent as i64],
                |r| Ok((r.get::<_, i64>(0)? as u64, r.get::<_, String>(1)?)),
            ).ok()?;
            parts.push(gn);
            name   = "".into();
            parent = gp;
        }
        parts.reverse();
        Some(format!("/{}", parts.join("/")))
    }
}
```

`path_for_inode` is used by `write_fd` to construct the event path. It is O(depth) and only runs when at least one watcher exists (caller short-circuits otherwise).

